text: Šárka Barborková (born 6 November 1985) is a Czech volleyball player. She played at the 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2011 Women's European Volleyball Championship, and 2011 Women's European Volleyball League. She played for Rote Raben Vilsbiburg. == References == Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
